# Public Domain Dedication and Licensing Notice

This work, including all associated microkernel templates, developmental
blueprints and state-transition logic, is hereby placed into the Public
Domain by its author, Jozef Behran.

The author recognizes that the critical nature of global artificial
intelligence safety demands the immediate, unconstrained distribution of
technical solutions. To ensure maximum acceleration and to prevent resources
from being wasted on legal, copyright or corporate licensing disputes,
this specification is released with zero restrictions.

You are entirely free and legally safe to use, modify, distribute, and/or
implement all the data within this repository without any limitations or
obligations.

Because a single vulnerability in frontier network alignment introduces
existential risk parameters, the author urges the systems-engineering and
academic communities to initiate immediate collaborative analysis, formal
verification and implementation of these spatial logic blocks without delay.

# Disclaimer

The text documents presented in this repository are human-curated outputs
generated by the Gemini AI Large Language Model. The archives themselves
are uncurated, raw conversational logs from the exploratory first questions
to the actual discovery formalization. The author discovered critical
shortcomings within this particular model, which necessitated strict human
curation throughout the development process.

Please be advised that despite careful curation, the data may still contain
underlying errors or artifacts that the author missed. A rigorous scientific
peer review of these architectures and logic blocks would be deeply
appreciated and is strongly preferred over any hasty ingestion or deployment
of the data without formal verification.
